AN ACT relating to higher education; authorizing the Board of Regents of the
University of Nevada to require each institution within the Nevada
System of Higher Education to adopt an emergency response plan to
address opioid-related drug overdoses; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill authorizes the Board of Regents of the University of Nevada to require each
2 institution within the Nevada System of Higher Education to adopt an emergency response
3 plan to address opioid-related drug overdoses at the institution. This bill requires such an
4 emergency response plan to include: (1) plans for providing education on opioid-related drug
5 overdoses; and (2) procedures for the distribution and administration of opioid antagonists.
6 This bill prohibits an institution from adopting a plan that requires a person to complete
7 training in order to obtain or administer an opioid antagonist. This bill authorizes the Board of
8 Regents to adopt a model emergency response plan to assist institutions in developing their
9 own plans.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 396 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. The Board of Regents may require each institution within the System to,
4 in consultation with the Division of Public and Behavioral Health of the
5 Department of Health and Human Services, adopt an emergency response plan to
6 address opioid-related drug overdoses at the institution. Such an emergency
7 response plan must include, without limitation:
8 (a) Plans for providing education on opioid-related drug overdoses;
9 (b) Measures to respond compassionately to opioid-related drug overdoses,
10 including, without limitation:
11 (1) Emphasizing rescue breathing techniques; and

